David Tennant Scoops Best Supporting Actor Award for You Me & Him At Lady Filmmakers Festival

caption:
David Tennant Scoops Best Supporting Actor Award for You Me & Him At Lady Filmmakers Festival 

David Tennant has picked up the award for Best Supporting Actor in a Feature for his role as John in You Me And Him during a very successful night for the 2017 comedy feature. The award was presented at the culmination of the 10th Lady Filmmakers Festival in Hollywood during the ‘Under The Stars’ gala in Beverley Hills on Sunday.

summary:
Behind The Scenes Of HBO's Camping With David Tennant, Jennifer Garner And The Rest Of The Star Studded Cast

  

HBO has...
caption:
Behind The Scenes Of HBO’s Camping With David Tennant, Jennifer Garner And The Rest Of The Star Studded Cast

HBO has released a behind the scenes look at their new comedy Camping, which stars David Tennant and Jennifer Garner as Walt and Kathryn, a married couple embarking on a fraught weekend to celebrate Walt’s 45th birthday. The show is based on the UK show of the same name created by Julia Davis and is an original limited series from Jenni Konner and Lena Dunham, the team behind Girls.

summary:
David Tennant Attends Amazon Prime Showcase For Good Omens In London 

David Tennant attended the Amazon Prime Showcase in...
caption:
David Tennant Attends Amazon Prime Showcase For Good Omens In London

David Tennant attended the Amazon Prime Showcase in London at the Curzon in Mayfair earlier today. He was there to promote Good Omens, the six-part TV adaptation of the comic apocalyptic novel by Neil Gaiman and Sir Terry Pratchett. The series has been written by Neil Gaiman and stars David Tennant as Crowley, ‘Hell’s most approachable demon’, and Michael Sheen as his counterpart, the fussy angel and rare book dealer Aziraphale. Neil and Michael were also guests on the panel today alongside the show’s director Douglas Mackinnon and fellow actors Miranda Richardson and Jon Hamm.  

Continue reading
